2016–17 UTAH JAZZ SEASON
The 2016–17 Utah Jazz season was the 43rd season of the franchise in the National Basketball Association ( NBA ) , and the 38th season of the franchise in Salt Lake City .
They qualified for the playoffs for the first time since 2012 .
The Jazz finished the regular season with a 51–31 record , securing the 5th seed .
In the playoffs , the Jazz defeated the Los Angeles Clippers in the First Round in seven games and advanced to the Western Conference Semifinals , where they were swept in four games by the Golden State Warriors .
Following the season , Gordon Hayward would sign as a free agent with the Boston Celtics .
He was also selected to play in the 2017 NBA All - Star Game .
